This paper deals with designing scheduling policies for wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves analyzing the performance of these policies, which can be considered as an information theory problem (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper deals with decentralized policies, which can be seen as a distributed computing problem (cs.DC). The paper also involves optimizing the performance of the network, which can be considered as a control systems problem (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves simulations and analysis, which can be seen as a machine learning problem (cs.MA).
